# Security Monitoring

This repository was bootstrapped with `wefidevkits` security monitoring.

## What Runs

- `Semgrep` scans the main executable source paths in this repository.
- `Gitleaks` scans the repository for hard-coded secrets.
- `Trivy` scans the repository filesystem for dependency vulnerabilities and high-risk misconfiguration.

## What Blocks A PR

- Any `Semgrep` finding from either the public JavaScript/Node.js/Python rulesets or the repository-local rules in `.semgrep/wefidevkits.yml`
- Any `Gitleaks` finding outside the allowlisted placeholder and documentation paths in `.gitleaks.toml`
- Any `Trivy` `HIGH` or `CRITICAL` vulnerability or misconfiguration, with `ignore-unfixed` enabled to reduce noise from issues with no published remediation yet

## Recommended Branch Protection

To make the checks enforceable, set these GitHub checks as required on your default branch:

- `semgrep`
- `gitleaks`
- `trivy`

